1
00:00:01,401 --> 00:00:04,503
[ethereal music]

2
00:00:04,505 --> 00:00:12,811
♪

3
00:00:17,517 --> 00:00:21,787
- THE WORLD HAS CHANGED.

4
00:00:25,091 --> 00:00:29,695
A BLOOD VIRUS
HAS PLAGUED US ALL.

5
00:00:33,299 --> 00:00:35,667
IT TAKES YOUR SOUL

6
00:00:35,669 --> 00:00:39,271
AND DESTROYS YOU
FROM THE INSIDE.

7
00:00:41,841 --> 00:00:47,379
IT SPREAD FROM TICKS,
THROUGH BIRDS AND DEER

8
00:00:47,381 --> 00:00:49,148
TO HUMANS.

9
00:00:49,150 --> 00:00:52,818
EVERYONE IS A CARRIER
OF ONE STRAIN OR ANOTHER,

10
00:00:52,820 --> 00:00:57,156
ONE STEP AWAY
FROM A DEADLY COMBINATION,

11
00:00:57,158 --> 00:00:59,625
A TICKING TIME BOMB.

12
00:00:59,627 --> 00:01:02,394
YOU CAN TRY TO CONTROL
THE FEVERS,

13
00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:04,797
GIVE YOUR IMMUNE SYSTEM
A CHANCE,

14
00:01:04,799 --> 00:01:07,533
BUT YOU'RE FIGHTING
THE UNKNOWN,

15
00:01:07,535 --> 00:01:12,137
SOMETHING THAT
WILL RIP YOU APART FROM WITHIN,

16
00:01:12,139 --> 00:01:13,405
SOMETHING ANIMAL,

17
00:01:13,407 --> 00:01:16,442
SOMETHING INHUMAN.

18
00:01:16,444 --> 00:01:19,311
BEFORE WE CAN REBUILD,
WE HAVE TO FIND A WAY

19
00:01:19,313 --> 00:01:21,447
TO SURVIVE OURSELVES,

20
00:01:21,449 --> 00:01:22,548
A WAY TO FIGHT.

21
00:01:22,550 --> 00:01:25,818
[bluesy rock music]

22
00:01:25,820 --> 00:01:34,259
♪

23
00:02:03,389 --> 00:02:11,663
♪

24
00:02:49,302 --> 00:02:52,704
[door rattling]

25
00:02:58,211 --> 00:03:00,679
[gun cocks]

26
00:03:00,681 --> 00:03:04,449
[pounding and rustling]

27
00:03:08,354 --> 00:03:10,455
[glass shattering]

28
00:03:13,893 --> 00:03:15,994
- THEY'RE EVERYWHERE, LOUIS!

29
00:03:15,996 --> 00:03:17,396
EVERYWHERE!

30
00:03:17,398 --> 00:03:18,263
[glass shatters]

31
00:03:18,265 --> 00:03:21,500
[driving rock music]

32
00:03:21,502 --> 00:03:29,808
♪

33
00:03:48,928 --> 00:03:57,436
♪

34
00:04:09,515 --> 00:04:11,984
- [whimpering]
WE'RE GONNA DIE!

35
00:04:11,986 --> 00:04:13,485
- YOU SHUT UP!

36
00:04:13,487 --> 00:04:15,988
YOU SHUT THE FUCK UP!

37
00:04:15,990 --> 00:04:18,590
RIGHT NOW,
WE ALL GOT TO KEEP OUR HEADS.

38
00:04:18,592 --> 00:04:20,993
IT'S NOT THE TIME
FOR THAT.

39
00:04:20,995 --> 00:04:24,463
WE HAVE TO FIGHT
AND SURVIVE!

40
00:04:24,465 --> 00:04:25,697
WE GOT TO BUTTON
THIS PLACE UP

41
00:04:25,699 --> 00:04:27,532
AND COVER UP THESE DOORS
AND WINDOWS.

42
00:04:27,534 --> 00:04:29,901
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THE HELL
IS OUT THERE,

43
00:04:29,903 --> 00:04:31,637
BUT IT'S COMING BACK.

44
00:04:31,639 --> 00:04:33,505
IT'S COMING BACK.

45
00:04:33,507 --> 00:04:36,308
COMING BACK.
IT'S FUCKING HUNGRY.

46
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:37,075
WE'RE NOT GONNA DIE.

47
00:04:37,077 --> 00:04:39,745
I'LL KILL EVERY SINGLE ONE
OF THOSE SONS OF BITCHES.

48
00:04:39,747 --> 00:04:40,979
ANDREW,
GO FIND EVERYTHING YOU CAN

49
00:04:40,981 --> 00:04:43,715
TO PUT ON THESE DOORS
AND WINDOWS,

50
00:04:43,717 --> 00:04:46,852
TABLES, CHAIRS,
ANYTHING.

51
00:04:46,854 --> 00:04:48,954
MATT, YOU WITH ME?

52
00:04:48,956 --> 00:04:51,923
- [groaning and panting]

53
00:04:51,925 --> 00:04:54,526
I AM STILL IN ONE PIECE.

54
00:04:54,528 --> 00:04:56,862
- WELL, STAY THAT WAY.

55
00:04:56,864 --> 00:05:01,433
GO GET THE AMMO.
LOAD UP THE GUNS.

56
00:05:01,435 --> 00:05:03,035
- LET'S DO SOMETHING.

57
00:05:03,037 --> 00:05:04,970
- DON'T ANYBODY DO ANYTHING

58
00:05:04,972 --> 00:05:08,540
WITHOUT TELLING ME FIRST!

59
00:05:10,510 --> 00:05:12,844
- EVERYTHING IS GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT.

60
00:05:12,846 --> 00:05:14,980
[glass shatters,
roaring]

61
00:05:22,388 --> 00:05:25,791
[twangy acoustic guitar music]

62
00:05:25,793 --> 00:05:34,099
♪

63
00:05:56,823 --> 00:06:00,425
[knife pounding]

64
00:06:05,064 --> 00:06:06,965
[gun cocks]

65
00:06:09,102 --> 00:06:12,738
[gun cocking]

66
00:06:18,911 --> 00:06:21,847
I SUPPOSE YOU'RE...

67
00:06:22,482 --> 00:06:28,019
JUST GONNA STAND AROUND MOPING
ALL WEEKEND, HUH?

68
00:06:28,021 --> 00:06:30,856
- THAT'S PRETTY MUCH
THE PLAN.

69
00:06:35,428 --> 00:06:38,563
- THAT'S TOO BAD.

70
00:06:38,565 --> 00:06:40,899
I WAS KIND OF HOPING
MAYBE WE'D HAVE

71
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:47,806
TIME TO TALK ABOUT THINGS
AND HAVE A FEW LAUGHS.

72
00:06:49,709 --> 00:06:51,109
I'M A FUNNY GUY.

73
00:06:51,111 --> 00:06:52,511
[laughs]

74
00:06:52,513 --> 00:06:55,514
RIGHT?

75
00:06:55,516 --> 00:06:56,448
I TOLD ANGELA

76
00:06:56,450 --> 00:06:58,650
THIS WASN'T GONNA BE
A GOOD IDEA,

77
00:06:58,652 --> 00:07:01,987
THIS WHOLE WEEKEND.

78
00:07:01,989 --> 00:07:05,657
- THIS WAS HER IDEA?
- YEAH.

79
00:07:05,659 --> 00:07:06,792
- [scoffs]

80
00:07:06,794 --> 00:07:07,526
WOW.

81
00:07:07,528 --> 00:07:10,662
- YOU KNOW, SHE'S A WOMAN,

82
00:07:10,664 --> 00:07:12,798
STARTING A RELATIONSHIP,

83
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,065
BUILDING A FAMILY.

84
00:07:14,067 --> 00:07:14,800
- [scoffs]

85
00:07:14,802 --> 00:07:17,836
OH, MY GOD,
YOU'RE PATHETIC.

86
00:07:17,838 --> 00:07:20,005
- YOU KNOW?

87
00:07:20,007 --> 00:07:21,640
WHAT ARE YOU DOING SMOKING
BY THE WAY?

88
00:07:21,642 --> 00:07:23,475
WHAT THE HELL?
WHEN DID YOU START THAT?

89
00:07:23,477 --> 00:07:26,111
TAKE THIS
OUT OF YOUR FUCKING HAND.

90
00:07:26,113 --> 00:07:27,946
- [scoffs]

91
00:07:27,948 --> 00:07:30,782
[shooter headphones
clatter and ding]

92
00:07:33,186 --> 00:07:34,653
I'M GONNA GO
UP TO THE LODGE

93
00:07:34,655 --> 00:07:38,256
AND SEE IF ANYBODY ELSE
IS HERE.

94
00:07:38,258 --> 00:07:41,626
- WHY DON'T YOU DO THAT?
- YEAH.

95
00:07:41,628 --> 00:07:45,163
[bluesy acoustic guitar
flourish]

96
00:07:45,165 --> 00:07:45,797
♪

97
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:48,633
- THAT'S THE WAY
OF THE WORLD, SON,

98
00:07:48,635 --> 00:07:49,768
A CIRCLE.

99
00:07:49,770 --> 00:07:52,938
IT'S BEEN GOING ON
SINCE THE BEGINNING OF TIME,

100
00:07:52,940 --> 00:07:55,173
SINCE MAN,
WITH STONE AND SPEAR,

101
00:07:55,175 --> 00:07:57,876
WENT OUT AND KILLED
HIS FIRST BEAST,

102
00:07:57,878 --> 00:07:59,244
MEAT AND FUR AND BONE.

103
00:07:59,246 --> 00:08:03,114
- BUT, DAD, WE DON'T NEED
TO DO THAT ANYMORE.

104
00:08:03,116 --> 00:08:03,849
WE HAVE STORES.

105
00:08:03,851 --> 00:08:06,318
- WELL, IMAGINE A WORLD
WITHOUT STORES.

106
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:07,018
CAN YOU?

107
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:09,988
A WORLD WITHOUT COMPUTERS
OR CELL PHONES

108
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:12,257
OR EVEN ELECTRICITY
FOR THAT MATTER.

109
00:08:12,259 --> 00:08:15,827
IN THAT WORLD, A MAN
WILL HAVE TO FEND FOR HIMSELF

110
00:08:15,829 --> 00:08:17,929
SO THAT HE AND HIS FAMILY
CAN SURVIVE.

111
00:08:17,931 --> 00:08:20,632
- COME ON, DAD,
THAT'S NEVER GONNA HAPPEN.

112
00:08:20,634 --> 00:08:22,868
- YOU NEVER KNOW, JEREMY.

113
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:24,603
YOU NEVER KNOW.

114
00:08:24,605 --> 00:08:25,704
I MEAN, IT WOULDN'T TAKE MUCH

115
00:08:25,706 --> 00:08:28,273
TO THROW THIS CRAZY WORLD
OFF BALANCE,

116
00:08:28,275 --> 00:08:29,574
AND IF THAT WERE TO HAPPEN,

117
00:08:29,576 --> 00:08:33,545
ONLY THE STRONG, THE SMART,
AND THE CAPABLE WOULD SURVIVE.

118
00:08:33,547 --> 00:08:36,948
- YOU'RE STARTING TO SOUND
LIKE ONE OF THOSE SURVIVAL NUTS.

119
00:08:36,950 --> 00:08:38,783
- [chuckles]

120
00:08:38,785 --> 00:08:40,151
AH.

121
00:08:40,153 --> 00:08:42,020
YOU AND YOUR
HAPLESS GENERATION

122
00:08:42,022 --> 00:08:44,856
OF TWEETER AND FACEBOOK
AND SKYPERS.

123
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:46,958
I'M AFRAID IF ANYTHING
WERE TO REALLY HAPPEN,

124
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:52,931
YOU'D ALL END UP RUNNING AROUND
LIKE A HOARD OF BLIND MICE.

125
00:08:55,735 --> 00:08:58,303
HEY, LOOK.

126
00:08:58,305 --> 00:09:00,705
- WHERE?

127
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:04,309
- RIGHT THERE,
HE'S LOOKING AT YOU.

128
00:09:04,311 --> 00:09:07,612
- I SEE HIM.

129
00:09:07,614 --> 00:09:09,648
[gunshot]

130
00:09:09,650 --> 00:09:10,916
- NEVER HESITATE, SON.

131
00:09:10,918 --> 00:09:15,854
THAT'S THE DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN SURVIVING OR NOT.

132
00:09:20,159 --> 00:09:23,762
[twangy acoustic guitar music]

133
00:09:23,764 --> 00:09:32,070
♪

134
00:09:34,173 --> 00:09:36,708
- ANDREW.

135
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:39,678
THE HELL YOU DOING?

136
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:48,119
YOU'RE ONE--
- LOUIS!

137
00:09:48,121 --> 00:09:49,688
- [laughs]

138
00:09:49,690 --> 00:09:51,189
LOOK WHO'S HERE.

139
00:09:51,191 --> 00:09:52,290
HEY!

140
00:09:52,292 --> 00:09:53,725
- [laughs]

141
00:09:53,727 --> 00:09:55,660
ANDREW,
HOW THE HELL ARE YOU, SON?

142
00:09:55,662 --> 00:09:58,296
- HEY, DOCTOR DENNEHEY,
HOW'VE YOU BEEN?

143
00:09:58,298 --> 00:09:59,864
- FINE, SON, FINE.

144
00:09:59,866 --> 00:10:01,132
YOU IN COLLEGE NOW?

145
00:10:01,134 --> 00:10:03,702
- I WENT FOR A WHILE.
- I SEE.

146
00:10:03,704 --> 00:10:06,338
JEREMY, SEE WHO'S HERE?

147
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:07,405
LOUIS.

148
00:10:07,407 --> 00:10:08,306
- HEY.
- HEY.

149
00:10:08,308 --> 00:10:10,809
- YOU OLD SON OF A BITCH,
HOW'VE YOU BEEN FARING?

150
00:10:10,811 --> 00:10:12,077
- GOOD, DOCTOR.
- YEAH? GOOD.

151
00:10:12,079 --> 00:10:14,846
YOU LOOK GOOD.
- WELL, THANKS.

152
00:10:14,848 --> 00:10:15,680
SO DO YOU.

153
00:10:15,682 --> 00:10:16,348
- YEAH, WHAT CAN I SAY?

154
00:10:16,350 --> 00:10:18,116
FIGHTING GRAVITY'S
A BITCH.

155
00:10:18,118 --> 00:10:20,352
- [laughing]

156
00:10:20,354 --> 00:10:22,988
YEAH, IT GETS HARDER
ALL THE TIME.

157
00:10:22,990 --> 00:10:23,722
- THAT IT DOES.

158
00:10:23,724 --> 00:10:25,991
- LOOKS LIKE
YOU'RE GETTING STARTED EARLY.

159
00:10:25,993 --> 00:10:27,325
- YEAH, YEAH,
I GUESS I HAVE.

160
00:10:27,327 --> 00:10:30,261
LOOKS LIKE YOU'RE
GETTING STARTED EARLY YOURSELF.

161
00:10:30,263 --> 00:10:32,831
- BREAKFAST OF CHAMPIONS.
- MM.

162
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:33,398
[both chuckle]

163
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,933
- WELL,
I'M GONNA TAKE OLD BUGS HERE,

164
00:10:34,935 --> 00:10:36,735
CUT HIM UP,
AND GET HIM READY FOR THE FIRE.

165
00:10:36,737 --> 00:10:39,337
TRY TO SAVE ME
ONE OF THOSE BEERS, HUH?

166
00:10:39,339 --> 00:10:42,374
- THERE'S PLENTY LEFT.

167
00:10:42,376 --> 00:10:44,209
ANDREW.

168
00:10:44,211 --> 00:10:47,212
WE ARE NOT DONE TALKING YET.

169
00:10:47,214 --> 00:10:51,249
YOU FIND SOME TIME
FOR YOUR FATHER,

170
00:10:51,251 --> 00:10:54,853
YOU LET ME KNOW.

171
00:10:54,855 --> 00:10:55,887
THE HELL YOU DOING?

172
00:10:55,889 --> 00:10:59,024
SITTING AROUND,
TAKING PICTURES?

173
00:11:05,865 --> 00:11:09,134
[bluesy guitar music]

174
00:11:09,136 --> 00:11:14,939
♪

175
00:11:19,311 --> 00:11:23,014
[whimsical music]

176
00:11:23,883 --> 00:11:25,383
- I'M SORRY, WAIT.

177
00:11:25,385 --> 00:11:27,118
ARE YOU SURE THIS IS OKAY?

178
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:30,055
- RELAX.
STEP INTO MY OFFICE.

179
00:11:30,057 --> 00:11:31,923
- OKAY.

180
00:11:31,925 --> 00:11:40,231
♪

181
00:11:46,305 --> 00:11:47,739
IS THERE POISON IVY?

182
00:11:47,741 --> 00:11:49,074
'CAUSE I GOT IT BAD ONCE,

183
00:11:49,076 --> 00:11:51,276
AND I HAD TO TAKE STEROIDS
FOR IT.

184
00:11:51,278 --> 00:11:54,846
NOT LIKE JACKED STEROIDS,
BUT IT WAS--

185
00:11:54,848 --> 00:11:55,947
- YOU GOT THE MONEY?
- OH.

186
00:11:55,949 --> 00:11:58,416
- BUSINESS BEFORE PLEASURE,
HONEY.

187
00:11:58,418 --> 00:12:00,985
- OH, YEAH.

188
00:12:06,459 --> 00:12:07,959
IS THIS ENOUGH?

189
00:12:07,961 --> 00:12:10,929
- THAT'S PLENTY.

190
00:12:10,931 --> 00:12:13,264
- OKAY.

191
00:12:15,501 --> 00:12:17,202
WOW.

192
00:12:17,204 --> 00:12:19,404
JESUS.

193
00:12:19,406 --> 00:12:21,239
DO YOU--CAN--

194
00:12:21,241 --> 00:12:24,275
I HAVE TO GO
TO THE BATHROOM.

195
00:12:43,863 --> 00:12:46,998
[mysterious breathing]

196
00:12:51,971 --> 00:12:54,105
[snarling]

197
00:12:57,276 --> 00:12:59,043
- HELLO?

198
00:12:59,045 --> 00:13:00,411
[snarling]

199
00:13:00,413 --> 00:13:04,015
[screaming]

200
00:13:19,865 --> 00:13:22,400
- WELL, SINCE YOU'RE FEELING
ALL DOMESTICATED,

201
00:13:22,402 --> 00:13:24,536
MAYBE YOU'D LIKE
TO HELP ME DISEMBOWEL

202
00:13:24,538 --> 00:13:25,436
THIS LITTLE FELLA.

203
00:13:25,438 --> 00:13:28,339
- OH, JESUS CHRIST, ED,
ON THE COUNTER LIKE THAT?

204
00:13:28,341 --> 00:13:28,973
FUCK.

205
00:13:28,975 --> 00:13:30,575
- LOOKING
A LITTLE JITTERY THERE, SETH.

206
00:13:30,577 --> 00:13:35,914
YOU KNOW, A FELLOW LIKE YOU
OUGHTN'T DRINK COFFEE.

207
00:13:35,916 --> 00:13:36,881
- YEAH, IS THAT A FACT?

208
00:13:36,883 --> 00:13:40,385
- I SAW JESSICA OUTSIDE,
BY THE WAY.

209
00:13:40,387 --> 00:13:43,121
HOW ARE YOU TWO
GETTING ALONG?

210
00:13:43,123 --> 00:13:44,556
- ACTUALLY NOT TOO GOOD.

211
00:13:44,558 --> 00:13:46,591
I MEAN,
WHAT CAN I SAY, ED?

212
00:13:46,593 --> 00:13:48,126
I'M A SHITTY BROTHER.

213
00:13:48,128 --> 00:13:50,028
- YOU SAID IT.
I DIDN'T.

214
00:13:50,030 --> 00:13:54,365
SURE YOU DON'T WANT TO HAVE A GO
WITH THAT?

215
00:13:54,367 --> 00:13:56,601
- I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO DO ANY OF THIS SHIT.

216
00:13:56,603 --> 00:13:58,069
- TYPICAL.
EH.

217
00:13:58,071 --> 00:14:01,940
ALL YOU GOT TO DO
IS TAKE CARE OF YOUR OWN NEEDS.

218
00:14:01,942 --> 00:14:05,210
SHITTY COFFEE,
BY THE WAY.

219
00:14:05,212 --> 00:14:06,511
KELLY!

220
00:14:06,513 --> 00:14:07,912
HOW ARE YOU, DARLING?
- HI.

221
00:14:07,914 --> 00:14:10,381
- SORRY I CAME IN EARLY
ON YOU HERE.

222
00:14:10,383 --> 00:14:11,382
- NO, NO, THAT'S OKAY.

223
00:14:11,384 --> 00:14:13,918
YOU KNOW, I REALLY SHOULD'VE
HAD THESE BEDS MADE.

224
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:16,387
I KNOW HOW YOU ARE,
DOCTOR DENNEHEY.

225
00:14:16,389 --> 00:14:17,956
HI.

226
00:14:17,958 --> 00:14:18,590
- SOMETHING WRONG?

227
00:14:18,592 --> 00:14:20,491
- IT'S JUST MY GRANDMA.
SHE'S BEEN SICK.

228
00:14:20,493 --> 00:14:22,260
I'VE BEEN TAKING CARE OF HER.

229
00:14:22,262 --> 00:14:23,394
- IS SHE OKAY?

230
00:14:23,396 --> 00:14:25,296
- YEAH, SHE'S GONNA BE FINE.

231
00:14:25,298 --> 00:14:26,998
RIGHT?

232
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:27,565
[sighs]

233
00:14:27,567 --> 00:14:28,600
I DON'T KNOW.

234
00:14:28,602 --> 00:14:30,568
- WELL, IF YOU'D LIKE,
I'LL GET MY BAG,

235
00:14:30,570 --> 00:14:31,569
AND WE'LL HAVE A LOOK.

236
00:14:31,571 --> 00:14:32,570
- WOULD YOU MIND DOING THAT?

237
00:14:32,572 --> 00:14:34,906
I MEAN, IT WOULD MAKE ME FEEL
SO MUCH BETTER.

238
00:14:34,908 --> 00:14:38,376
- OH, MY PLEASURE, DARLING.

239
00:14:38,378 --> 00:14:39,344
- OH, BY THE WAY,

240
00:14:39,346 --> 00:14:41,246
I'M SORRY
ABOUT YOUR GRANDFATHER.

241
00:14:41,248 --> 00:14:43,615
HE WAS A GOOD MAN.

242
00:14:47,419 --> 00:14:48,152
- HEY, GRANDMA.

243
00:14:48,154 --> 00:14:49,988
THERE'S SOMEONE HERE
TO SEE YOU.

244
00:14:49,990 --> 00:14:51,256
- [gasping sporadically]

245
00:14:51,258 --> 00:14:53,691
- HI, GRANDMA ANNIE.

246
00:14:53,693 --> 00:14:57,395
- [gasping weakly]

247
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:02,033
- IT'S GETTING WORSE.

248
00:15:02,035 --> 00:15:04,535
- IT'S ME, DOCTOR DENNEHEY.

249
00:15:04,537 --> 00:15:06,271
I UNDERSTAND
YOU'RE NOT FEELING WELL.

250
00:15:06,273 --> 00:15:08,606
CAN YOU TELL ME
WHAT'S AILING YOU?

251
00:15:08,608 --> 00:15:11,376
- [gasping weakly]

252
00:15:11,378 --> 00:15:13,311
- I'M GONNA TAKE HER TEMPERATURE

253
00:15:13,313 --> 00:15:17,415
AND CHECK HER VITALS,
OKAY?

254
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:19,350
HEY THERE, SWEETHEART.

255
00:15:19,352 --> 00:15:20,585
JUST OPEN UP.

256
00:15:20,587 --> 00:15:22,420
THERE YOU GO.

257
00:15:22,422 --> 00:15:24,689
HOLD IT RIGHT THERE.

258
00:15:33,132 --> 00:15:34,032
- [whimpers]

259
00:15:34,034 --> 00:15:36,601
- YEAH, SHE'S BURNING UP.

260
00:15:36,603 --> 00:15:37,735
YEAH.

261
00:15:37,737 --> 00:15:40,405
AND HER PULSE IS ELEVATED.

262
00:15:40,407 --> 00:15:43,975
HERE, LET ME SEE.

263
00:15:43,977 --> 00:15:46,144
OH, MY GOSH, 104.

264
00:15:46,146 --> 00:15:47,679
- IS SHE GONNA BE OKAY?

265
00:15:47,681 --> 00:15:50,114
- YEAH, SHE'LL BE FINE.

266
00:15:50,116 --> 00:15:52,617
WHAT I'D RECOMMEND,
YOU KNOW,

267
00:15:52,619 --> 00:15:53,351
WE KEEP HER BED,

268
00:15:53,353 --> 00:15:55,253
GIVE HER LOTS OF LIQUIDS
AND FOOD.

269
00:15:55,255 --> 00:15:57,121
IF YOU LIKE,
I CAN GIVE HER SOMETHING

270
00:15:57,123 --> 00:15:59,057
TO HELP HER SLEEP.

271
00:15:59,059 --> 00:16:00,558
YEAH?

272
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:05,163
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE FINE,
GRANDMA ANNIE.

273
00:16:05,165 --> 00:16:06,230
- [gasping weakly]

274
00:16:06,232 --> 00:16:08,366
- CAN YOU HEAR ME, ANNIE?

275
00:16:08,368 --> 00:16:11,469
- [wheezes]

276
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,107
[gasping weakly]

277
00:16:16,109 --> 00:16:19,410
- HERE YOU GO, HONEY.
THIS IS GONNA HELP YOU.

278
00:16:19,412 --> 00:16:21,612
HERE YOU GO.
JUST OPEN YOUR MOUTH.

279
00:16:21,614 --> 00:16:24,282
[ominous droning music]

280
00:16:24,284 --> 00:16:26,050
- GRANDMA,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

281
00:16:26,052 --> 00:16:28,186
- [gasping weakly]

282
00:16:28,188 --> 00:16:30,621
- ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

283
00:16:30,623 --> 00:16:33,057
- I'M FINE.

284
00:16:33,059 --> 00:16:37,362
- I'M GONNA GET SOME BANDAGES.

285
00:16:37,364 --> 00:16:45,570
♪

286
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:50,742
[percussive music]

287
00:16:50,744 --> 00:16:59,283
♪

288
00:17:17,503 --> 00:17:25,810
♪

289
00:17:41,693 --> 00:17:44,362
- BEAUTIFUL DAY, BOYS.

290
00:17:44,364 --> 00:17:45,596
- YOU READY?

291
00:17:45,598 --> 00:17:47,231
- DON'T MIND IF I DO.

292
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:48,232
CHERRY, I MEANT TO ASK YOU,

293
00:17:48,234 --> 00:17:50,468
YOU BUY THAT STOCK I TOLD YOU
ABOUT LAST YEAR?

294
00:17:50,470 --> 00:17:54,105
HOPE YOU DID.
IT WENT THROUGH THE ROOF.

295
00:17:54,107 --> 00:17:56,140
- I'M SORRY TO SAY I DIDN'T.

296
00:17:56,142 --> 00:17:57,542
WHAT'D YOU DO?

297
00:17:57,544 --> 00:18:00,478
- WELL, YOU KNOW ME.
BOUGHT LOW, SOLD HIGH.

298
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:01,212
MADE A KILLING.

299
00:18:01,214 --> 00:18:03,648
SPEAKING OF KILLING,
ANYBODY WANT TO GO HUNTING?

300
00:18:03,650 --> 00:18:04,782
- HOW IS SHE?
- WHO?

301
00:18:04,784 --> 00:18:05,850
- KELLY'S GRANDMOTHER.

302
00:18:05,852 --> 00:18:09,287
- OH, SHE'LL BE FINE.
JUST A LITTLE TOUCH OF THE FLU.

303
00:18:09,289 --> 00:18:10,688
SHALL WE?

304
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:12,256
- I'M SO IN.

305
00:18:12,258 --> 00:18:12,890
- WELL, LUCKY US.

306
00:18:12,892 --> 00:18:16,761
HEY, CHERRY, WAS THAT YOU
FIRING OFF ROUNDS BEFORE?

307
00:18:16,763 --> 00:18:18,596
- I'M JUST A LITTLE BIT
OUT OF PRACTICE.

308
00:18:18,598 --> 00:18:21,532
- DON'T LISTEN TO HIM,
HE'S BEST DAMN RIFLE SHOT

309
00:18:21,534 --> 00:18:22,867
I EVER KNEW.

310
00:18:22,869 --> 00:18:24,535
- [laughs]

311
00:18:24,537 --> 00:18:25,570
THAT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

312
00:18:25,572 --> 00:18:28,239
- LONG AGO BUT NOT FORGOTTEN,
PAL.

313
00:18:28,241 --> 00:18:28,773
COME ON.

314
00:18:28,775 --> 00:18:29,841
BEASTS ARE WAITING.

315
00:18:29,843 --> 00:18:31,209
- LET'S HAVE AT IT.

316
00:18:31,211 --> 00:18:34,612
[twangy acoustic guitar music]

317
00:18:34,614 --> 00:18:37,648
♪

318
00:18:37,650 --> 00:18:40,218
- JEREMY, WE'RE GOING OUT
FOR A WHILE.

319
00:18:40,220 --> 00:18:41,319
YOU WANT TO COME ALONG
WITH US,

320
00:18:41,321 --> 00:18:44,522
OR YOU WANT TO HANG
WITH THE OTHER KIDS?

321
00:18:44,524 --> 00:18:45,389
- I DON'T KNOW.

322
00:18:45,391 --> 00:18:49,861
- COME ON.
- WHERE ARE THE OTHER KIDS?

323
00:18:49,863 --> 00:18:53,831
- THEY'LL PROBABLY BE BACK SOON,
RIGHT?

324
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:54,532
- COME ON.

325
00:18:54,534 --> 00:18:56,901
COME ON, I NEED MY WINGMAN,
YEAH?

326
00:18:56,903 --> 00:18:59,670
GET OFF YOUR ASS, BOY.

327
00:19:04,877 --> 00:19:05,843
HOPE YOU DON'T MIND.

328
00:19:05,845 --> 00:19:10,715
I SET THAT UP AS YOUR QUARTERS
THIS WEEKEND.

329
00:19:10,717 --> 00:19:12,683
[laughs]

330
00:19:13,819 --> 00:19:15,920
- AN UNSPEAKABLE TRAGEDY
HAS BEFALLEN

331
00:19:15,922 --> 00:19:17,355
A GROUP OF LOCAL BOY SCOUTS

332
00:19:17,357 --> 00:19:18,322
ON A WEEKEND CAMPING TRIP

333
00:19:18,324 --> 00:19:20,458
IN THE AREA
OF THE NEHANTIC STATE FOREST

334
00:19:20,460 --> 00:19:22,260
IN EAST LYME, CONNECTICUT,
TODAY.

335
00:19:22,262 --> 00:19:24,829
SEVERAL BOYS FROM THE GROUP
OF TEN SENIOR SCOUTS

336
00:19:24,831 --> 00:19:27,865
ON A LOCAL HIGH ADVENTURE TRIP
FOR THE WEEKEND

337
00:19:27,867 --> 00:19:29,734
HAVE DISAPPEARED
INTO THE WOODS

338
00:19:29,736 --> 00:19:30,835
AND HAVE YET TO BE FOUND.

339
00:19:30,837 --> 00:19:34,205
FOUR OTHER MEMBERS OF
BOY SCOUT TROOP 26 FROM OLD LYME

340
00:19:34,207 --> 00:19:36,741
HAVE BEEN HOSPITALIZED
FOR UNDISCLOSED SYMPTOMS

341
00:19:36,743 --> 00:19:39,911
AT LAWRENCE MEMORIAL HOSPITAL
IN OLD SAYBROOK

342
00:19:39,913 --> 00:19:41,979
AFTER AN APPARENT ANIMAL ATTACK.

343
00:19:41,981 --> 00:19:43,614
LOCAL DOCTORS SAY
THE SICKNESS

344
00:19:43,616 --> 00:19:45,716
APPEARS TO BE RELATED
TO LYME DISEASE

345
00:19:45,718 --> 00:19:47,652
THAT WAS LIKELY CONTRACTED
BY THE BOYS

346
00:19:47,654 --> 00:19:51,422
BECAUSE OF EXPOSURE
TO INFECTED WILDLIFE.

347
00:19:51,424 --> 00:19:58,262
- SO WHAT'S BEEN HAPPENING
IN YOUR WORLD?

348
00:19:58,264 --> 00:20:00,831
- GOT DUMPED RECENTLY.

349
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:02,800
- OUCH.
- HOW ABOUT YOU?

350
00:20:02,802 --> 00:20:05,403
BOYFRIEND?
- YEAH.

351
00:20:05,405 --> 00:20:06,671
IT'S NOTHING SERIOUS, THOUGH.

352
00:20:06,673 --> 00:20:10,575
IT'S SOMETHING
TO PASS THE TIME.

353
00:20:10,577 --> 00:20:13,611
- YOU KNOW THEY SHOT A SCENE
IN <i>RETURN OF THE JEDI</i>

354
00:20:13,613 --> 00:20:14,645
ON THIS TREE?

355
00:20:14,647 --> 00:20:15,379
- OH, YEAH?

356
00:20:15,381 --> 00:20:18,783
- THE SCENE WITH PRINCESS LEIA
AND THE EWOK.

357
00:20:18,785 --> 00:20:21,886
THEY MEET RIGHT HERE
FOR A CANDY BAR.

358
00:20:21,888 --> 00:20:26,390
- THAT'S A LOT OF HISTORY.

359
00:20:26,392 --> 00:20:28,025
SO...

360
00:20:29,027 --> 00:20:33,931
WHAT HAPPENED WITH THE CHICK?

361
00:20:33,933 --> 00:20:34,799
- SHE BROKE UP WITH ME,

362
00:20:34,801 --> 00:20:38,970
AND AFTER TWO YEARS
OF PUTTING UP WITH--

363
00:20:38,972 --> 00:20:40,671
- WHAT?
- JESUS.

364
00:20:40,673 --> 00:20:42,273
I DON'T WANT TO GET INTO IT.

365
00:20:42,275 --> 00:20:42,940
- WELL, YOU HAVE TO NOW.

366
00:20:42,942 --> 00:20:45,276
- IT'S ACTUALLY
QUITE EMBARRASSING.

367
00:20:45,278 --> 00:20:48,546
- COME ON.

368
00:20:48,548 --> 00:20:50,881
- SHE'S SAVING HERSELF.

369
00:20:50,883 --> 00:20:53,484
- WHAT?

370
00:20:53,486 --> 00:20:56,454
SO YOU NEVER--

371
00:20:56,456 --> 00:20:57,521
- NO.

372
00:20:57,523 --> 00:20:58,289
- [chuckles]

373
00:20:58,291 --> 00:21:03,661
- I'VE GOT MYSELF A SET
OF SEVERELY SWOLLEN BLUE BALLS.

374
00:21:03,663 --> 00:21:04,729
- I BET YOU DO.

375
00:21:04,731 --> 00:21:06,964
- IN FACT,
SITTING LIKE THIS RIGHT NOW

376
00:21:06,966 --> 00:21:08,332
IS QUITE UNCOMFORTABLE.

377
00:21:08,334 --> 00:21:11,569
LIKE, I HAVE TO READJUST.

378
00:21:11,571 --> 00:21:13,471
- POOR THING.

379
00:21:13,473 --> 00:21:15,539
- BUT ENOUGH ABOUT MY BALLS.

380
00:21:15,541 --> 00:21:16,474
- [laughs]

381
00:21:16,476 --> 00:21:18,075
- DO YOU HAVE A JOB,
OR YOU JUST RUN AROUND

382
00:21:18,077 --> 00:21:19,810
PHOTOGRAPHING PEOPLE
IN THE WOODS?

383
00:21:19,812 --> 00:21:23,814
- I WORK AS A CASHIER.
- OH.

384
00:21:23,816 --> 00:21:25,483
- IT'S VERY EXCITING.

385
00:21:25,485 --> 00:21:27,785
- WELL,
SOMEBODY'S GOT TO DO IT.

386
00:21:27,787 --> 00:21:29,086
- YEAH.

387
00:21:29,088 --> 00:21:31,822
I GUESS SO.

388
00:21:31,824 --> 00:21:32,957
WHAT DO YOU DO?

389
00:21:32,959 --> 00:21:34,792
- I WORK AT A GARAGE.

390
00:21:34,794 --> 00:21:35,926
- AH.

391
00:21:35,928 --> 00:21:39,063
- DO YOU RIDE MOTORCYCLES?
- NO.

392
00:21:39,065 --> 00:21:41,632
BUT I LIKE GUYS
WHO DO.

393
00:21:41,634 --> 00:21:43,701
- AH, OF COURSE.

394
00:21:43,703 --> 00:21:45,936
- [laughs]

395
00:22:02,087 --> 00:22:04,021
- DID YOU HEAR THAT?

396
00:22:10,462 --> 00:22:11,462
[gunshot]

397
00:22:11,464 --> 00:22:14,031
- [laughs]

398
00:22:14,033 --> 00:22:16,634
- [laughs]

399
00:22:23,108 --> 00:22:25,076
- OH, LOOK.

400
00:22:25,078 --> 00:22:26,610
- AW.
- SHH.

401
00:22:26,612 --> 00:22:30,915
- IT'S CUTE.

402
00:22:30,917 --> 00:22:35,019
[warbling tone,
mysterious growling]

403
00:22:36,021 --> 00:22:39,457
[energetic rock music]

404
00:22:39,459 --> 00:22:44,962
♪

405
00:22:53,739 --> 00:22:54,805
HEY.

406
00:22:54,807 --> 00:22:57,775
- I SUPPOSE YOU WANT
TO TALK NOW, IS THAT IT?

407
00:22:57,777 --> 00:23:00,444
- DO DEER EAT MEAT?

408
00:23:02,914 --> 00:23:04,014
- NOT THAT I KNOW OF.

409
00:23:04,016 --> 00:23:06,851
- WE JUST A SAW A DEER
KILL A SQUIRREL

410
00:23:06,853 --> 00:23:09,620
AND EATS ITS GUTS.

411
00:23:09,622 --> 00:23:11,722
- [laughs]

412
00:23:11,724 --> 00:23:14,692
I THINK THE TWO OF YOU
ARE PROBABLY SMOKING

413
00:23:14,694 --> 00:23:16,026
MORE THAN JUST CIGARETTES.

414
00:23:16,028 --> 00:23:17,695
- THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

415
00:23:17,697 --> 00:23:23,634
GRAZING BEASTS DON'T KILL
OTHER GRAZING BEASTS FOR MEAT.

416
00:23:23,636 --> 00:23:25,703
LOUIS,

417
00:23:25,705 --> 00:23:27,004
YOUR BUCK.

418
00:23:27,006 --> 00:23:29,874
CARE TO DO THE HONORS?

419
00:23:29,876 --> 00:23:30,741
- I'M SORRY, ED.

420
00:23:30,743 --> 00:23:33,911
IF YOU'D LIKE TO TAKE CARE
OF THAT FOR ME.

421
00:23:33,913 --> 00:23:35,846
YOU ARE THE SURGEON.

422
00:23:35,848 --> 00:23:36,914
- MY PLEASURE.

423
00:23:36,916 --> 00:23:38,616
JUST PROMISE ME
YOU'RE NOT GONNA TURN

424
00:23:38,618 --> 00:23:42,787
INTO ONE
OF THESE HOPELESS VEGETARIANS.

425
00:23:42,789 --> 00:23:45,956
- I PROMISE.

426
00:23:52,497 --> 00:23:54,165
- LOOK, DAD,

427
00:23:54,167 --> 00:23:56,801
WE'RE NOT LYING.

428
00:23:59,237 --> 00:24:02,506
- YOU KNOW,
A LOT OF STRANGE THINGS HAPPEN

429
00:24:02,508 --> 00:24:04,241
OUT IN THE WOODS.

430
00:24:04,243 --> 00:24:05,176
- [gasping weakly]

431
00:24:05,178 --> 00:24:06,744
♪ HUSH LITTLE BABY

432
00:24:06,746 --> 00:24:09,246
♪ DON'T SAY A WORD ♪

433
00:24:09,248 --> 00:24:11,081
♪ MAMA'S GONNA BUY YOU ♪

434
00:24:11,083 --> 00:24:12,650
♪ A MOCKINGBIRD

435
00:24:12,652 --> 00:24:17,788
♪ AND IF THAT MOCKINGBIRD
DON'T SING ♪

436
00:24:17,790 --> 00:24:18,789
[wheezes deeply]

437
00:24:18,791 --> 00:24:23,194
♪ MAMA'S GONNA BUY YOU
A DIAMOND RING ♪

438
00:24:23,196 --> 00:24:24,862
[gasps]

439
00:24:26,832 --> 00:24:29,133
[coughs]

440
00:24:29,135 --> 00:24:32,570
[ominous droning music]

441
00:24:32,572 --> 00:24:40,878
♪

442
00:24:44,549 --> 00:24:47,718
[twangy acoustic guitar music]

443
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:50,020
- FLOWS LIKE A RIVER.

444
00:24:51,957 --> 00:24:55,993
PRETTY SOON, IT'S JUST GONNA BE
VENISON STEAK.

445
00:24:57,829 --> 00:24:59,563
- SO COOL.

446
00:24:59,565 --> 00:25:01,665
- WELL, IT LOOKS LIKE
YOU'VE FOUND SOMETHING

447
00:25:01,667 --> 00:25:02,833
OTHER THAN COMPUTERS
YOU LIKE.

448
00:25:02,835 --> 00:25:05,903
MAYBE YOU'LL CONSIDER
FOLLOWING IN MY FOOTSTEPS

449
00:25:05,905 --> 00:25:07,204
AND BECOMING A SURGEON.

450
00:25:07,206 --> 00:25:10,774
GRAB ON THEM LEGS
REAL TIGHT, BOYS.

451
00:25:11,743 --> 00:25:13,577
ALL RIGHTY.

452
00:25:19,885 --> 00:25:21,118
[laughs]

453
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:24,121
- [coughing]

454
00:25:24,123 --> 00:25:25,222
- [chortles]

455
00:25:25,224 --> 00:25:27,324
HEY, WHERE YOU GOING?

456
00:25:27,326 --> 00:25:28,559
SHE'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

457
00:25:28,561 --> 00:25:31,228
GRAB BACK ON THAT LEG.

458
00:25:31,230 --> 00:25:33,197
THIS WAS A GOOD BEAST.

459
00:25:33,199 --> 00:25:36,300
IT'S GONNA FEED MANY.

460
00:25:36,302 --> 00:25:39,970
JESUS CHRIST, WHAT THE HELL
IS THIS OVER HERE?

461
00:25:39,972 --> 00:25:42,072
- WHERE?

462
00:25:42,074 --> 00:25:43,307
- AH!

463
00:25:43,309 --> 00:25:44,975
- FUCKING ASSHOLE, ED.

464
00:25:44,977 --> 00:25:47,044
- [laughing heartily]

465
00:25:47,046 --> 00:25:50,748
BETTER FETCH ME
ANOTHER BUCKET, JEREMY.

466
00:25:54,819 --> 00:25:59,089
GONNA BE NOTHING BUT GOOD
EATING THE REST OF THIS NIGHT.

467
00:25:59,091 --> 00:26:00,691
THERE YOU GO.

468
00:26:00,693 --> 00:26:01,725
HUH?
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

469
00:26:01,727 --> 00:26:03,794
MAKE LITTLE SAUSAGES
OUT OF THAT?

470
00:26:03,796 --> 00:26:04,762
- [laughs]

471
00:26:04,764 --> 00:26:06,730
- [chuckles]

472
00:26:11,903 --> 00:26:15,105
KILLING BAMBI.

473
00:26:15,107 --> 00:26:18,309
[ambient music playing]

474
00:26:18,311 --> 00:26:21,979
♪

475
00:26:25,717 --> 00:26:28,285
[tires squeal]

476
00:26:34,726 --> 00:26:37,861
[ominous ethereal music]

477
00:26:37,863 --> 00:26:46,170
♪

478
00:26:48,139 --> 00:26:50,307
- HELLO?

479
00:26:54,980 --> 00:26:58,115
HELLO?

480
00:27:00,151 --> 00:27:03,287
HELLO?

481
00:27:05,123 --> 00:27:07,224
HEY.

482
00:27:07,226 --> 00:27:10,794
HEY, IT'S OKAY.
HI.

483
00:27:10,796 --> 00:27:14,798
ARE YOU OKAY?

484
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:16,133
- ARE YOU SICK?

485
00:27:16,135 --> 00:27:17,768
- NO, HONEY.

486
00:27:17,770 --> 00:27:19,670
I'M NOT SICK.

487
00:27:19,672 --> 00:27:21,405
- ARE YOU SURE?

488
00:27:21,407 --> 00:27:23,774
- YEAH, I'M SURE.

489
00:27:23,776 --> 00:27:28,445
LISTEN, MY NAME'S ANGELA.
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

490
00:27:28,447 --> 00:27:30,681
- SARAH.

491
00:27:30,683 --> 00:27:31,982
- ALL RIGHT, SARAH.

492
00:27:31,984 --> 00:27:33,017
I WANT TO GET YOU OUT OF HERE.

493
00:27:33,019 --> 00:27:34,718
I DON'T THINK
WE'RE SAFE HERE,

494
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:36,220
SO WOULD YOU COME WITH ME?

495
00:27:36,222 --> 00:27:37,788
I'LL TAKE CARE OF YOU.

496
00:27:37,790 --> 00:27:39,123
DON'T WORRY.

497
00:27:39,125 --> 00:27:40,858
OKAY?

498
00:27:40,860 --> 00:27:41,859
YEAH, COME ON.

499
00:27:41,861 --> 00:27:44,028
IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

500
00:27:44,030 --> 00:27:44,895
COME ON.

501
00:27:44,897 --> 00:27:47,731
THAT'S A GOOD GIRL.

502
00:27:47,733 --> 00:27:49,299
GOOD.

503
00:27:49,301 --> 00:27:51,268
- [sighs]

504
00:27:51,270 --> 00:27:54,838
[panting]

505
00:27:58,476 --> 00:28:01,812
[eerie music]

506
00:28:01,814 --> 00:28:05,249
♪

507
00:28:05,251 --> 00:28:08,318
UH-OH.

508
00:28:10,121 --> 00:28:12,156
UH-OH.

509
00:28:13,024 --> 00:28:16,393
[panting]

510
00:28:20,832 --> 00:28:22,966
[gravel scraping]

511
00:28:22,968 --> 00:28:24,968
SARAH?

512
00:28:24,970 --> 00:28:27,204
♪

513
00:28:27,206 --> 00:28:28,105
SARAH?

514
00:28:28,107 --> 00:28:29,406
- ARE YOU OUT HERE
BY YOURSELF?

515
00:28:29,408 --> 00:28:31,875
WHERE'S YOUR MOM AND DAD?

516
00:28:33,745 --> 00:28:37,014
[metal clattering and crashing]

517
00:28:39,818 --> 00:28:42,953
[ominous music]

518
00:28:42,955 --> 00:28:51,228
♪

519
00:28:53,031 --> 00:28:56,900
- HEY, THAT'S MY GIRL, YEAH.

520
00:28:56,902 --> 00:28:57,401
[coughs]

521
00:28:57,403 --> 00:29:00,938
- WHAT?
YOU'RE HER FATHER?

522
00:29:00,940 --> 00:29:03,941
- YES.

523
00:29:03,943 --> 00:29:05,375
YES, I AM.

524
00:29:05,377 --> 00:29:06,276
[coughs]

525
00:29:06,278 --> 00:29:10,180
- WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH YOU?
- I'M FINE.

526
00:29:10,182 --> 00:29:11,348
[coughs]

527
00:29:11,350 --> 00:29:16,386
- YOU DON'T LOOK FINE.

528
00:29:16,388 --> 00:29:18,155
- COME HERE, HONEY.

529
00:29:18,157 --> 00:29:19,790
[panting]

530
00:29:19,792 --> 00:29:20,891
COME HERE.

531
00:29:20,893 --> 00:29:22,392
[snarls]

532
00:29:22,394 --> 00:29:23,494
COME HERE, BABY.

533
00:29:23,496 --> 00:29:25,028
- YOU DON'T LOOK ALL RIGHT.

534
00:29:25,030 --> 00:29:26,296
THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG.

535
00:29:26,298 --> 00:29:28,398
- COME TO DADDY, HONEY.

536
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:31,869
IT'S COLD OUT.

537
00:29:31,871 --> 00:29:33,237
[snorts]

538
00:29:33,239 --> 00:29:35,806
COME--COME--COME--COME--

539
00:29:35,808 --> 00:29:39,943
COME TO DADDY.
COME TO DADDY.

540
00:29:39,945 --> 00:29:41,478
I WANT MY KID BACK.

541
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:43,547
- YOU'RE SCARING ME.
YOU'RE GONNA SCARE HER.

542
00:29:43,549 --> 00:29:44,948
WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH YOU?

543
00:29:44,950 --> 00:29:46,517
- I HAVE A CONDITION.
I HAVE A--

544
00:29:46,519 --> 00:29:48,952
I HAVEN'T HAD
MY MEDICATION TODAY,

545
00:29:48,954 --> 00:29:49,953
SO I'M A LITTLE JUMPY,

546
00:29:49,955 --> 00:29:52,289
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
I CAN'T BE A FATHER

547
00:29:52,291 --> 00:29:54,958
TO MY OWN CHILD,
SO CAN YOU JUST PLEASE

548
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:57,127
LET ME HAVE MY KID, OKAY?

549
00:29:57,129 --> 00:29:57,828
- NO, NO.

550
00:29:57,830 --> 00:30:00,030
SARAH, YOUR DADDY'S
NOT YOUR DADDY ANYMORE.

551
00:30:00,032 --> 00:30:03,400
STAY HERE WITH ME.
- COME ON OVER, PLEASE.

552
00:30:03,402 --> 00:30:04,168
[snarls]

553
00:30:04,170 --> 00:30:05,869
- NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

554
00:30:05,871 --> 00:30:09,106
I'M GONNA TAKE HER WITH ME.

555
00:30:09,108 --> 00:30:10,541
- HONEY.

556
00:30:10,543 --> 00:30:12,075
GET OVER HERE.

557
00:30:12,077 --> 00:30:12,943
- HE'S MY DAD.

558
00:30:12,945 --> 00:30:14,578
- NO, THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG
WITH HIM.

559
00:30:14,580 --> 00:30:16,880
WE HAVE TO GO FIND HIM
SOME HELP, OKAY?

560
00:30:16,882 --> 00:30:17,581
YOU JUST COME WITH ME.

561
00:30:17,583 --> 00:30:20,017
- NO, YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.
- NO, I KNOW.

562
00:30:20,019 --> 00:30:20,918
I KNOW YOU WANT SEE HIM.

563
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:24,421
HE LOOKS LIKE YOUR DAD,
BUT HE'S NOT YOUR DAD.

564
00:30:24,423 --> 00:30:26,590
- COME TO DADDY.

565
00:30:48,379 --> 00:30:50,614
[growls softly]

566
00:30:53,918 --> 00:30:55,118
- NO!

567
00:30:55,120 --> 00:30:57,487
- [snarling]

568
00:30:59,090 --> 00:31:00,490
[both snarl]

569
00:31:03,228 --> 00:31:05,662
[engine revs, tires screech]

570
00:31:05,664 --> 00:31:07,297
[fire crackling]

571
00:31:07,299 --> 00:31:10,567
[eerie ambient music]

572
00:31:10,569 --> 00:31:19,076
♪

573
00:31:27,185 --> 00:31:30,621
[twangy acoustic guitar music]

574
00:31:30,623 --> 00:31:33,557
♪

575
00:31:33,559 --> 00:31:38,295
- BLOOD RARE,
THE WAY GOD MEANT IT TO BE.

576
00:31:38,297 --> 00:31:40,464
YOU SURE YOU DON'T WANT ME
TO THROW ONE OF THESE

577
00:31:40,466 --> 00:31:43,233
ON THE FIRE
FOR YOU THERE, LOUIS?

578
00:31:43,235 --> 00:31:46,603
- I THINK I'M GONNA STAY
ON A LIQUID DIET.

579
00:31:46,605 --> 00:31:47,337
- SUIT YOURSELF.

580
00:31:47,339 --> 00:31:50,040
PASS ME ONE OF THOSE BEERS,
WILL YOU?

581
00:31:58,016 --> 00:31:58,515
[chuckles]

582
00:31:58,517 --> 00:32:01,718
MY, MY, YOU'RE SMELLING
PRETTY GOOD THERE, BOY.

583
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:05,656
- HE WENT TO A TURKISH BATH.
IT'S RIGHT DOWN THE ROAD.

584
00:32:05,658 --> 00:32:07,691
[chuckling]

585
00:32:07,693 --> 00:32:10,694
COME ON BACK.
WE'RE GONNA MAKE S'MORES.

586
00:32:10,696 --> 00:32:13,096
[both laughing]

587
00:32:13,098 --> 00:32:17,234
- YOU KNOW, YOUR SON OVER THERE
IS SMITTEN.

588
00:32:17,236 --> 00:32:20,270
- HORMONES.

589
00:32:23,474 --> 00:32:31,982
♪

590
00:32:34,686 --> 00:32:37,287
- JEREMY!

591
00:32:37,289 --> 00:32:38,989
SUPPER'S ON!

592
00:32:38,991 --> 00:32:41,591
COME AND GET IT!

593
00:32:43,494 --> 00:32:46,263
FEAST TOGETHER...

594
00:32:46,265 --> 00:32:49,066
ALL RIGHT, LET'S EAT.

595
00:32:50,735 --> 00:32:55,105
- I THINK MY FEET
ARE ON FIRE.

596
00:33:00,511 --> 00:33:05,582
- SO YOU'RE A VEGETARIAN TOO.

597
00:33:05,584 --> 00:33:10,354
- WELL, YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE MISSING THERE, LOUIS.

598
00:33:10,356 --> 00:33:12,456
COOKED IT UP FOR YOU,
MY LIEGE.

599
00:33:12,458 --> 00:33:16,193
- LOOKS PERFECT.

600
00:33:16,195 --> 00:33:19,262
- THANKS FOR GETTING HER,
EAGLE EYE.

601
00:33:19,264 --> 00:33:22,566
BLESS THIS FALLEN BEAST,
FOR 'OUT HIM,

602
00:33:22,568 --> 00:33:25,202
THERE WILL BE NO FEAST.

603
00:33:25,204 --> 00:33:27,504
- BON APPETIT.

604
00:33:27,506 --> 00:33:31,174
- THAT'S GOOD.
THAT IS GOOD.

605
00:33:31,176 --> 00:33:34,578
[twangy acoustic guitar music]

606
00:33:34,580 --> 00:33:41,151
♪

607
00:33:41,153 --> 00:33:43,420
- YOU'RE A BETTER MAN THAN I,
GUNGA DIN.

608
00:33:43,422 --> 00:33:46,289
AFTER JEREMY'S MOM,
I'VE BEEN IN NO HURRY

609
00:33:46,291 --> 00:33:48,158
TO JUMP BACK IN THE FIRE.

610
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:50,060
FIRM BACHELORHOOD FOR ME.

611
00:33:50,062 --> 00:33:52,829
ANOTHER ONE?
- SURE, WHY NOT?

612
00:33:52,831 --> 00:33:55,298
HOW MANY TIMES YOU BEEN MARRIED,
ED?

613
00:33:55,300 --> 00:33:56,533
- [chuckles]

614
00:33:56,535 --> 00:33:57,367
THREE, MY FRIEND,

615
00:33:57,369 --> 00:33:59,102
AND THREE STRIKES,
YOU'RE OUT.

616
00:33:59,104 --> 00:34:03,373
ONLY GOOD THING TO COME OUT
OF IT ALL WAS JEREMY.

617
00:34:03,375 --> 00:34:05,675
SETH, WHY DON'T YOU
GO BACK THERE IN YOUR ROOM

618
00:34:05,677 --> 00:34:08,445
AND FETCH US
THAT BOTTLE OF NAPOLEON BRANDY

619
00:34:08,447 --> 00:34:11,448
YOU GOT HIDDEN?

620
00:34:11,450 --> 00:34:12,382
- ALL RIGHT.

621
00:34:12,384 --> 00:34:13,250
- AND AFTER THAT,

622
00:34:13,252 --> 00:34:14,351
WHY DON'T YOU CHOP SOME WOOD?

623
00:34:14,353 --> 00:34:18,488
I MEAN, WHAT, ARE WE SUPPOSED
TO DO ALL THE WORK AROUND HERE?

624
00:34:21,292 --> 00:34:23,427
WHY THE FUCK
DOES THIS GUY COME HERE?

625
00:34:23,429 --> 00:34:25,162
- YOU KNOW,
THIS WHOLE NEW KID THING

626
00:34:25,164 --> 00:34:27,664
IS MAKING ME PRETTY NERVOUS,

627
00:34:27,666 --> 00:34:30,400
CONSIDERING I DIDN'T DO
A VERY GOOD JOB

628
00:34:30,402 --> 00:34:31,468
FIRST TIME AROUND.

629
00:34:31,470 --> 00:34:33,804
- IT'S NEVER TOO LATE
TO GET IT RIGHT.

630
00:34:33,806 --> 00:34:37,374
HERE'S TO HAVING THE BALLS
TO TRY.

631
00:34:37,376 --> 00:34:38,575
[glasses clink]

632
00:34:38,577 --> 00:34:41,344
- THANK YOU, ED.

633
00:34:42,346 --> 00:34:44,114
[mysterious shrill tone]

634
00:34:44,116 --> 00:34:45,649
- WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH YOU?

635
00:34:45,651 --> 00:34:48,885
- NOTHING, I JUST FEEL
A LITTLE LIGHT-HEADED.

636
00:34:48,887 --> 00:34:51,354
- YOU ALL RIGHT?

637
00:34:51,356 --> 00:34:51,755
- YEAH.

638
00:34:51,757 --> 00:34:53,890
- WHAT THE FUCK HAPPENED
TO YOUR HAND?

639
00:34:53,892 --> 00:34:56,660
- OH, NOTHING,
JUST A SCRATCH.

640
00:34:56,662 --> 00:34:58,695
FUNNY, THOUGH.

641
00:34:58,697 --> 00:35:01,531
KELLY'S GRANDMA BIT ME.

642
00:35:01,533 --> 00:35:03,467
- SHE SURE DID.

643
00:35:03,469 --> 00:35:05,902
WHAT, IS SHE FUCKING SENILE?

644
00:35:05,904 --> 00:35:09,539
- HERE YOU GO, GUYS.

645
00:35:09,541 --> 00:35:11,308
- YEAH, I WORRY.

646
00:35:11,310 --> 00:35:14,511
I GOT A FEELING
THIS WILL DO THE TRICK.

647
00:35:14,513 --> 00:35:15,779
- [laughing]
OKAY.

648
00:35:15,781 --> 00:35:16,613
- [laughs]

649
00:35:16,615 --> 00:35:17,581
- POUR AWAY.
- YEAH.

650
00:35:17,583 --> 00:35:19,483
LET ME SCURRY THAT ONE UP
FOR YOU.

651
00:35:19,485 --> 00:35:20,450
- MM-HMM.

652
00:35:20,452 --> 00:35:21,218
- [chuckles]

653
00:35:21,220 --> 00:35:22,953
- HERE'S TO THOSE HUNGRY
COUNTRY GIRLS.

654
00:35:22,955 --> 00:35:28,225
- OH, MY GOODNESS.
- YEAH, THAT'S THE GOOD STUFF.

655
00:35:28,227 --> 00:35:31,495
- MAKES ME FEEL YOUNG AGAIN.

656
00:35:37,268 --> 00:35:38,401
- [coughs]

657
00:35:38,403 --> 00:35:39,903
[sniffles]

658
00:35:41,639 --> 00:35:43,740
[spits]

659
00:35:56,687 --> 00:35:59,923
[eerie ambient music]

660
00:35:59,925 --> 00:36:08,431
♪

661
00:36:08,933 --> 00:36:10,500
- YO.
- DICK.

662
00:36:10,502 --> 00:36:12,802
- WHAT, ARE YOU GOING
TO A RAVE?

663
00:36:12,804 --> 00:36:13,670
- YOU'RE FUNNY.

664
00:36:13,672 --> 00:36:16,406
YOU WANT TO FIRE OFF
A COUPLE ROUNDS WITH ME?

665
00:36:16,408 --> 00:36:20,243
- FIRE OFF A COUPLE ROUNDS
OF THAT.

666
00:36:20,245 --> 00:36:21,645
- HERE YOU GO, MAN.

667
00:36:21,647 --> 00:36:24,915
BE CAREFUL WITH THAT.
IT'S REALLY GOOD.

668
00:36:24,917 --> 00:36:26,816
- OOH.

669
00:36:29,353 --> 00:36:30,287
- HOW YOU DOING, MAN?

670
00:36:30,289 --> 00:36:32,622
- I DON'T KNOW.
THIS FUCKING TRIP.

671
00:36:32,624 --> 00:36:36,960
MY DAD IS TRYING TO PACK IN
25 YEARS INTO A WEEKEND.

672
00:36:36,962 --> 00:36:39,996
IT'S NOT HAPPENING.

673
00:36:39,998 --> 00:36:42,866
- OH, MAN,
THE FUCKING DOCTOR.

674
00:36:42,868 --> 00:36:46,736
JESUS CHRIST, EVERY YEAR,
HE'S ALL OVER ME,

675
00:36:46,738 --> 00:36:47,571
EVERYTHING I DO.

676
00:36:47,573 --> 00:36:51,741
- "GRAZING BEASTS DON'T FEED ON
OTHER GRAZING BEASTS."

677
00:36:51,743 --> 00:36:52,742
- DID HE FUCKING SAY THAT?

678
00:36:52,744 --> 00:36:54,344
- WHAT THE FUCK
DOES THAT EVEN MEAN?

679
00:36:54,346 --> 00:36:56,580
- I BET HIS BLONDE HAIR
WAS LIKE--

680
00:36:56,582 --> 00:36:57,581
[imitates wind blowing]

681
00:36:57,583 --> 00:36:58,481
BLOWING IN THE WIND.

682
00:36:58,483 --> 00:37:00,584
I SWEAR TO GOD,
HE'S GOT A PERM.

683
00:37:00,586 --> 00:37:02,419
- HEY, LISTEN, MAN.

684
00:37:02,421 --> 00:37:04,521
I'M GONNA ASK YOU A QUESTION.
- WHAT'S THAT?

685
00:37:04,523 --> 00:37:08,792
- AND, TO ME,
THIS IS ALL THAT MATTERS.

686
00:37:08,794 --> 00:37:10,560
DID YOU BRING LORETTA?

687
00:37:10,562 --> 00:37:11,494
- [laughs]

688
00:37:11,496 --> 00:37:12,729
GET THE FUCK OVER HERE, KID.

689
00:37:12,731 --> 00:37:16,266
- HE SAID, "I DO EVERYTHING
EXCEPT FOR TWO THINGS.

690
00:37:16,268 --> 00:37:19,603
I DON'T KISS,
AND I DON'T SWALLOW."

691
00:37:19,605 --> 00:37:23,006
[both laughing]

692
00:37:27,345 --> 00:37:28,979
- OH, GOD,
THOSE WERE THE GOOD OLD DAYS

693
00:37:28,981 --> 00:37:31,281
WHEN WE WERE
IN THE SERVICE, LOUIS.

694
00:37:31,283 --> 00:37:34,718
AH, NO WORRIES.
CAREFREE.

695
00:37:34,720 --> 00:37:36,620
- IT WASN'T ALL FUN AND GAMES.

696
00:37:36,622 --> 00:37:37,520
THAT'S FOR SURE.

697
00:37:37,522 --> 00:37:42,359
- YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT, BUT
OTHER THAN WHAT WE HAD TO DO,

698
00:37:42,361 --> 00:37:43,660
IT WAS PRETTY CAREFREE.

699
00:37:43,662 --> 00:37:47,697
MAY WE NEVER HAVE TO GO
THAT WAY AGAIN, BUDDY.

700
00:37:47,699 --> 00:37:48,431
[glasses clink]

701
00:37:48,433 --> 00:37:50,967
- AH, TO BE YOUNG...
YOUNG AGAIN.

702
00:37:50,969 --> 00:37:54,571
- YOU KNOW, I'M NOT REALLY SURE
I CAN HANDLE THAT.

703
00:37:54,573 --> 00:37:56,773
- OH, I BET YOU COULD.

704
00:37:56,775 --> 00:37:58,375
LISTEN, I'M GONNA HIT IT.

705
00:37:58,377 --> 00:38:00,477
I GOT TO TURN IN.

706
00:38:00,479 --> 00:38:03,546
- GOOD SEEING YOU, PAL.
- YEAH.

707
00:38:03,548 --> 00:38:06,616
THERE'S ONLY ONE DOCTOR ED,
AND THAT'S YOU.

708
00:38:06,618 --> 00:38:08,785
- [laughs]

709
00:38:08,787 --> 00:38:11,488
[glasses clink]

710
00:38:11,490 --> 00:38:13,723
- NIGHTY NIGHT.

711
00:38:20,931 --> 00:38:24,668
[mysterious shrill tone]

712
00:38:27,004 --> 00:38:30,473
[eerie ambient music]

713
00:38:30,475 --> 00:38:34,944
♪

714
00:38:34,946 --> 00:38:36,613
- LORETTA LOO?

715
00:38:36,615 --> 00:38:41,518
SOMEONE'S HERE TO SEE YOU.

716
00:38:41,520 --> 00:38:44,721
YOU REMEMBER ANDREW.

717
00:38:44,723 --> 00:38:48,725
DOES SHE FEEL GOOD?
- OH, SHE'S SO BADASS.

718
00:38:48,727 --> 00:38:49,826
HO, HO.

719
00:38:49,828 --> 00:38:52,462
SHE LOOKS AMAZING.

720
00:38:52,464 --> 00:38:54,964
- WELL, HAVE AT IT, HOSS.

721
00:38:54,966 --> 00:38:56,866
- HEY, SETH.

722
00:38:56,868 --> 00:38:58,702
DO DEER EAT MEAT?

723
00:38:58,704 --> 00:39:00,003
- [laughs]

724
00:39:00,005 --> 00:39:00,904
NO.

725
00:39:00,906 --> 00:39:03,473
TOLD YOU
THAT SHIT WAS GOOD.

726
00:39:03,475 --> 00:39:06,743
[electronic ringtone]

727
00:39:06,745 --> 00:39:13,049
♪

728
00:39:13,051 --> 00:39:15,885
- OH.

729
00:39:15,887 --> 00:39:18,088
[sighs]

730
00:39:24,028 --> 00:39:27,797
[roaring monstrously]

731
00:39:29,667 --> 00:39:30,867
DID YOU GET MY--

732
00:39:30,869 --> 00:39:32,702
DID YOU GET MY CHECK?

733
00:39:32,704 --> 00:39:36,439
[panting painfully]

734
00:39:37,708 --> 00:39:39,442
[growling]

735
00:39:39,444 --> 00:39:40,610
HOW COME YOU DIDN'T CASH IT?

736
00:39:40,612 --> 00:39:42,579
I NOTICED YOU DIDN'T CASH IT.

737
00:39:42,581 --> 00:39:45,949
[growling]

738
00:39:47,184 --> 00:39:50,854
I'LL BE IN CHARGE
OF WHERE SHE IS!

739
00:39:50,856 --> 00:39:54,524
[sobbing quietly]

740
00:39:57,595 --> 00:40:00,597
NO, I DIDN'T FUCKING FEED HER,
ALL RIGHT?

741
00:40:00,599 --> 00:40:01,698
WHAT THE FUCK?

742
00:40:01,700 --> 00:40:03,700
OF COURSE I FED HER.

743
00:40:06,137 --> 00:40:07,937
SHE'S EATING.

744
00:40:07,939 --> 00:40:09,906
[snarls monstrously]

745
00:40:09,908 --> 00:40:13,510
[chewing loudly]

746
00:40:16,814 --> 00:40:20,784
YEAH, WHAT THE FUCK
DID I JUST SAY?

747
00:40:20,786 --> 00:40:24,187
[panting]

748
00:40:26,457 --> 00:40:30,860
SHE HAD ONE BITE, AND NOW
SHE'S HAVING ANOTHER BITE.

749
00:40:30,862 --> 00:40:32,529
OKAY?

750
00:40:32,531 --> 00:40:36,032
[sobbing quietly]

751
00:40:36,767 --> 00:40:40,770
OH, YOU MEAN THE POOL HOUSE
WHERE YOU FUCKED THE CABANA BOY?

752
